course.subject: CENG
course.name: Prototype Development for Chemical Processes and Products
course.description: A process and product design course for chemical and biological engineers via an experiential learning pedagogy. Students will learn to build prototypes of chemical products or miniaturized chemical processes incorporating chemical, biological, mechanical and electronic modules. Skills such as mathematical modeling, 3-D printing, Arduino programming, design and assembly of mechanical parts, data acquisition and processing, will be taught and practiced. Instructor's approval is required for enrollment in the course.
course.prerequisites: CENG 2110 OR COMP 1021 OR COMP 1022P OR ELEC 1100
